00:34:38.450 --> 00:34:44.070
And that was one of the
most incredible stories I've

00:34:44.070 --> 00:34:45.370
ever heard.

00:34:45.370 --> 00:34:47.100
And, I'll let Barry
finish up with that.

00:34:47.100 --> 00:34:49.500
&gt;&gt; Barry Bergey:
Well that story was,

00:34:49.500 --> 00:34:53.680
her family was living in Bosnia.

00:34:53.680 --> 00:34:57.320
And, she was about 17
years old at the time.

00:34:57.320 --> 00:34:58.880
And, her father could tell

00:34:58.880 --> 00:35:02.590
that the Holocaust
was on the horizon.

00:35:02.590 --> 00:35:07.010
And so, he had got her
a passport, somehow,

00:35:07.010 --> 00:35:10.510
a forged passport,
and he put her

00:35:10.510 --> 00:35:14.260
on the train with her accordion.

00:35:14.260 --> 00:35:17.850
And, he said just keep
playing the accordion

00:35:17.850 --> 00:35:21.620
and if the officials come up,
just keep playing the accordion

00:35:21.620 --> 00:35:25.010
and they may not
check your identity.

00:35:25.010 --> 00:35:30.370
And, she was able to
escape Bosnia and 42

00:35:30.370 --> 00:35:33.390
of her family members
were killed in the,

00:35:33.390 --> 00:35:34.760
including her grandmother,

00:35:34.760 --> 00:35:38.520
who is the person she
learned her songs from.

00:35:38.520 --> 00:35:44.100
So, she wanted to carry on, of
course, that family tradition.

00:35:44.100 --> 00:35:48.250
And, the accordion you see on
the right side of the screen,

00:35:48.250 --> 00:35:51.720
the little white according is
the accordion that she carried

00:35:51.720 --> 00:35:54.210
with her on that train ride.

00:35:54.210 --> 00:35:59.720
And, just recently, the Virginia
Foundation for the Humanities,

00:35:59.720 --> 00:36:04.950
the Folk Arts Program there, had
someone restore the accordion

00:36:04.950 --> 00:36:06.980
so she could play it again.

00:36:06.980 --> 00:36:09.590
But, it's quite a
story both tragic

00:36:09.590 --> 00:36:13.910
and has its happy
ending as well for her.

00:36:13.910 --> 00:36:16.500
&gt;&gt; Tom Pich: So, when she
was telling me this story,

00:36:16.500 --> 00:36:18.760
I asked her what
happened to the accordion,

00:36:18.760 --> 00:36:20.990
she said she still had it.

00:36:20.990 --> 00:36:25.070
