So, this was the only trip
I had been able to take

00:37:53.160 --> 00:37:56.340
with Tom and his journeys.

00:37:56.340 --> 00:37:59.460
&gt;&gt; Tom Pich: There was a
couple other funny stories.

00:37:59.460 --> 00:38:01.720
But, within that,
we got to the house

00:38:01.720 --> 00:38:04.560
and Wade's wife plays for him.

00:38:04.560 --> 00:38:06.930
So, I thought it was appropriate

00:38:06.930 --> 00:38:09.050
to photograph the
two of them together.

00:38:09.050 --> 00:38:12.290
And then, off we went
with this whole family.

00:38:12.290 --> 00:38:15.240
The house was full of
children and grandchildren

00:38:15.240 --> 00:38:16.540
and great grandchildren.

00:38:16.540 --> 00:38:20.840
And, off we went to the
local high school where,

00:38:20.840 --> 00:38:25.420
as you can see in the smaller
photograph, was full wall

00:38:25.420 --> 00:38:29.730
to wall with townspeople that
came out to hear them play

00:38:29.730 --> 00:38:33.860
and to honor him
for his birthday.

00:38:33.860 --> 00:38:36.580
Well, the ceremony
went on proceeding.

00:38:36.580 --> 00:38:42.170
And, I was off the side of the
stage taking some photographs.

00:38:42.170 --> 00:38:47.690
And, Wade came, after a song he
was trying to wave me to come

00:38:47.690 --> 00:38:50.510
on stage and I kept saying no.

00:38:50.510 --> 00:38:52.580
So finally, he said to the
audience, I'm not going

00:38:52.580 --> 00:38:54.130
to play unless Tom comes out.

00:38:54.130 --> 00:38:57.610
So, I came out, I stood next
to him, he introduced me,

00:38:57.610 --> 00:39:00.800
I said a couple of
things and all the sudden,

00:39:00.800 --> 00:39:06.160
someone in the audience just
stood up and said sit down.

00:39:06.160 --> 00:39:08.980
And, I was stunned.

00:39:08.980 --> 00:39:11.760
And, I looked at Barry in
the audience and my eyes were

00:39:11.760 --> 00:39:13.690
like this big, I froze.

00:39:13.690 --> 00:39:20.190
And somebody else shouted from
the audience and I'm like, wait,

00:39:20.190 --> 00:39:23.070
I got to get, I got to go,
I got to get off the stage.

00:39:23.070 --> 00:39:24.370
They want to hear you

00:39:24.370 --> 00:39:25.840
and they're telling
me to go sit down.

00:39:25.840 --> 00:39:29.770
And, I mean, so I left.

00:39:29.770 --> 00:39:33.310
And I was, it had me.

00:39:33.310 --> 00:39:34.610
And, I left the building.

00:39:34.610 --> 00:39:38.040
And Barry had seen me leave and
he met me out in the courtyard.

00:39:38.040 --> 00:39:40.500
And, I was like I didn't mean
to come out and I'm trying

00:39:40.500 --> 00:39:43.190
to explain myself that
Wade wanted me out there

00:39:43.190 --> 00:39:46.680
and I didn't mean to upset the
audience and stop the music.

00:39:46.680 --> 00:39:51.760
And, we went over to a cousin
or of Wades and we talked to him

00:39:51.760 --> 00:39:56.170
about it, you know, we
didn't mean to upset them

00:39:56.170 --> 00:40:01.560
and why the reaction in
the audience was so great.

00:40:01.560 --> 00:40:04.170
And he says, they weren't doing
that, they were asking for Wade

00:40:04.170 --> 00:40:08.220
to play the song Sit Down.

00:40:08.220 --> 00:40:10.520
&gt;&gt; Barry Bergey: There's a
great gospel song that Wade

00:40:10.520 --> 00:40:14.460
and Julia were well known
for where she says sit down

00:40:14.460 --> 00:40:15.850
and he says I can't sit down.

00:40:15.850 --> 00:40:18.190
She says sit down, he
says I can't sit down,

00:40:18.190 --> 00:40:21.110
she says sit down, I can't
sit down I just got to heaven

00:40:21.110 --> 00:40:22.780
and I got to walk around.

00:40:22.780 --> 00:40:24.880
So, that's what they
were calling for.

00:40:24.880 --> 00:40:26.600
&gt;&gt; Tom Pich: And I tell you
I would've been happy being

00:40:26.600 --> 00:40:28.500
in heaven at that moment.

00:40:28.500 --> 00:40:32.100
I don't know what, I
was, that was a tough,

00:40:32.100 --> 00:40:33.520
that was a tough moment.

00:40:33.520 --> 00:40:35.200
But I was relieved afterwards.

00:40:35.200 --> 00:40:39.740
So, the visits take on all
kinds of different directions

00:40:39.740 --> 00:40:46.120
and the stories become
more interesting

00:40:46.120 --> 00:40:47.740
than the photos sometimes.

00:40:47.740 --> 00:40:53.270
And a similar thing
happened with Chunky Sanchez.

00:40:53.270 --> 00:40:55.930
I know he wasn't
in great health.

00:40:55.930 --> 00:41:01.190
But, a week after he received
his Heritage fellowship in 2013,

00:41:01.190 --> 00:41:04.190
I flew out to San Diego to
visit with him, now I set it

00:41:04.190 --> 00:41:07.240
up with his family,
with his wife.

00:41:07.240 --> 00:41:09.550
And, I'm always at a location.

00:41:09.550 --> 00:41:11.870
So, we, I asked Chunky
where would you

00:41:11.870 --> 00:41:13.610
like to be photographed,
before I got out there?

00:41:13.610 --> 00:41:15.260
And, he said Chicano Park.

00:41:15.260 --> 00:41:17.520
Now, if anybody's
been in San Diego,

00:41:17.520 --> 00:41:20.970
there's wonderful
murals in this park.

00:41:20.970 --> 00:41:25.880
So, I arrived there about an
hour plus before I was supposed

00:41:25.880 --> 00:41:27.180
to meet Chunky.

00:41:27.180 --> 00:41:29.970
And, I was watching these,
all these cars pull up

00:41:29.970 --> 00:41:31.820
and families would get out.

00:41:31.820 --> 00:41:33.120
And then, they started putting

00:41:33.120 --> 00:41:37.090
on these costumes
and headdresses.

00:41:37.090 --> 00:41:40.490
So, of course I'm
interested, and I walk over

00:41:40.490 --> 00:41:42.950
and says is there
a parade today.

00:41:42.950 --> 00:41:46.640
And they said no we're
here to meet a friend.

00:41:46.640 --> 00:41:49.780
And, questions on questions,
and they said we're here

00:41:49.780 --> 00:41:53.430
to honor Chunky Sanchez.

00:41:53.430 --> 00:41:55.430
And I said how did you know
he was going to be here?

00:41:55.430 --> 00:41:57.060
Oh, his wife called us.

00:41:57.060 --> 00:42:01.620
And, he's such an advocate
for the different communities,

00:42:01.620 --> 00:42:07.140
for Mexico and the Aztec
communities, that they came

00:42:07.140 --> 00:42:10.410
to be, just to witness
me photographing him.

00:42:10.410 --> 00:42:12.630
And, that's when I realized,

00:42:12.630 --> 00:42:14.670
I couldn't just photograph
Chunky alone.

00:42:14.670 --> 00:42:16.810
I put them all in the photo.

00:42:16.810 --> 00:42:22.490
And, it just was incredible
how many people loved this man

00:42:22.490 --> 00:42:24.490
for them to show up.

00:42:24.490 --> 00:42:26.230
And, it's a much
better photograph

00:42:26.230 --> 00:42:30.110
than me just photographing
him alone.

00:42:30.110 --> 00:42:31.410
He's since passed away.

00:42:31.410 --> 00:42:35.170
